Loading Data.

Importing annotation

We import biological annotation from ENSEMBL

mart <- useMart(biomart = "ENSEMBL_MART_ENSEMBL",
                dataset = "hsapiens_gene_ensembl",
                host = 'https://www.ensembl.org')

ttg <- biomaRt::getBM(
  attributes = c("ensembl_gene_id", "external_gene_name", "description","entrezgene_id"),
  mart = mart)

Read count table and remove samples with less than 8 Millions of counts.

count_table <- read_tsv("counts.htseq")
## New names:
## Rows: 61857 Columns: 175
##  Column specification
##  Delimiter: "\t" chr
## (1): ...1 dbl (174): 01-018-A_S13_R1_001.sam, 01-020-A_S14_R1_001.sam,
## 01-021-B1_S19_R...
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data. 
## Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
##  `` -> `...1`
count_long <- count_table %>% 
  rename(gene_id =1) %>% 
  pivot_longer(names_to = "Sample", values_to = "counts", -gene_id) %>% 
  group_by(Sample) %>% 
  mutate(TotalCounts = sum(counts)) 

count_long %>% 
  dplyr::select(Sample, TotalCounts) %>% 
  distinct() %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = TotalCounts)) + geom_histogram()
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

count_8M <- count_long %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  filter(TotalCounts > 8e6) %>% 
  group_by(gene_id,Sample) %>% 
  summarise(counts = sum(counts)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  group_by(gene_id) %>% 
  mutate(TotalGene = sum(counts)) %>% 
  filter(TotalGene > 30) %>% 
  ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'gene_id'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
count_8M %>% 
  mutate(counts = counts+1) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=Sample, y = counts)) + geom_boxplot() + coord_flip() + scale_y_log10()

Modification of the metadata to match with counts data

metadata <- readxl::read_excel("/storage2/RNASeq/all/metadata.xlsx")


metadata <- count_8M %>% 
  dplyr::select(Sample) %>% distinct() %>% 
  mutate(Paciente = str_extract(Sample,"\\d+-\\d+")) %>% 
  mutate(Paciente = str_replace(Paciente,"8-021","08-021")) %>% 
  mutate(Paciente = str_replace(Paciente,"8-019","08-019")) %>% 
  inner_join(metadata) %>% 
  dplyr::rename(Respuesta = `Mejor respuesta`)
## Joining, by = "Paciente"

metadata %>%

Quality Control

To check the quality of the sample we test the homogenicity of the groups. In this case we represent the samples using Multi-Dimensional Scaling

mds <- counts(dds_gene, normalized = T) %>% 
  t()%>% vegdist(method = "bray") %>% 
  metaMDS()

To test the homogenicity we perform a PERMANOVA test

dist <- counts(dds_gene, normalized = T) %>% 
  t() %>% vegdist(method = "bray")

adonis2(dist ~ Respuesta, data = metadata, permutations = 10000)
## Permutation test for adonis under reduced model
## Terms added sequentially (first to last)
## Permutation: free
## Number of permutations: 10000
## 
## adonis2(formula = dist ~ Respuesta, data = metadata, permutations = 10000)
##           Df SumOfSqs     R2      F Pr(>F)
## Respuesta  3   0.2426 0.0438 0.8092 0.5448
## Residual  53   5.2974 0.9562              
## Total     56   5.5400 1.0000

The homogenicity of the groups is statistically significant so the sample quality is good enough

LRT test

lrt <- results(dds_gene_lrt) %>%  as_tibble(rownames = "ensembl_gene_id") %>% View()

EE vs NE

table_8M <- count_8M %>% 
  inner_join(metadata) %>% 
  filter(Respuesta == "EE" | Respuesta =="NE") %>% 
  dplyr::select(gene_id,Sample, counts) %>% 
  semi_join(metadata) %>% 
  pivot_wider(names_from = Sample, values_from = counts) %>% 
  as_data_frame() %>% 
  column_to_rownames("gene_id") %>% 
  as.matrix() 
## Joining, by = "Sample"
## Joining, by = "Sample"
dds_gene <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = table_8M, 
                                   colData = metadata %>% filter(Respuesta == "EE" | Respuesta =="NE"), 
                                   design = ~Respuesta)
## converting counts to integer mode
## Warning in DESeqDataSet(se, design = design, ignoreRank): some variables in
## design formula are characters, converting to factors
dds_gene <- DESeq(dds_gene, fitType = "parametric", sfType = "poscount")
## estimating size factors
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
## -- replacing outliers and refitting for 16294 genes
## -- DESeq argument 'minReplicatesForReplace' = 7 
## -- original counts are preserved in counts(dds)
## estimating dispersions
## fitting model and testing
EE_vs_NE <- results(dds_gene, contrast = c("Respuesta","EE","NE"))

EE_vs_NE <- EE_vs_NE %>% 
  as_tibble(rownames = "ensembl_gene_id") %>%
    rename(fdr = padj) %>% 
  mutate(bonferroni = p.adjust(pvalue, method = "bonferroni")) %>% 
  mutate(homl = p.adjust(pvalue, method = "holm")) %>% 
  mutate(BY = p.adjust(pvalue, method = "BY")) %>% 
  filter(grepl("ENS",ensembl_gene_id)) %>% 
  mutate(ensembl_gene_id = str_replace(ensembl_gene_id,"\\.\\d+","")) %>% 
  inner_join(ttg)
## Joining, by = "ensembl_gene_id"
EE_vs_NE %>% 
  mutate(sig = ifelse(fdr < 0.001,"Significative","No-Significative")) %>%
  mutate(label = ifelse(sig == "Significative",external_gene_name,NA)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x= log2FoldChange, y = -log10(fdr), color = sig, size = sqrt(baseMean), label = label)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_text_repel(size = 1.5)+
  scale_color_d3() +
  theme_light() + labs(title = "EE vs NE")
## Warning: Removed 26743 rows containing missing values (geom_point).
## Warning: Removed 46795 rows containing missing values (geom_text_repel).
## Warning: ggrepel: 120 unlabeled data points (too many overlaps). Consider
## increasing max.overlaps

EE_vs_NE_enr <- EE_vs_NE %>% 
  filter(fdr < 0.001) %>% inner_join(ttg) %>% 
  dplyr::select(entrezgene_id) %>% distinct() %>% drop_na() %>%  pull(entrezgene_id)
## Joining, by = c("ensembl_gene_id", "external_gene_name", "description",
## "entrezgene_id")
EE_vs_NE_enr_go <- enrichGO(gene =EE_vs_NE_enr,
                                   OrgDb         = org.Hs.eg.db,
                                    ont           = "ALL",
                                    pAdjustMethod = "BH",
                                    pvalueCutoff  = 0.01,
                                    qvalueCutoff  = 0.05,
                                    readable      = TRUE)

if ((EE_vs_NE_enr_go %>% as.data.frame() %>% nrow()) > 0  )
{
  barplot(EE_vs_NE_enr_go, showCategory = 20)
} else{
  print("No enriched GO")
}
## [1] "No enriched GO"
EE_vs_NE_enr_kegg <- enrichKEGG(gene = EE_vs_NE_enr,
                                        organism     = 'hsa',
                                        pvalueCutoff = 0.05)
## Reading KEGG annotation online:
## 
## Reading KEGG annotation online:

NE vs PE

table_8M <- count_8M %>% 
  inner_join(metadata) %>% 
  filter(Respuesta == "NE" | Respuesta =="PE") %>% 
  dplyr::select(gene_id,Sample, counts) %>% 
  semi_join(metadata) %>% 
  pivot_wider(names_from = Sample, values_from = counts) %>% 
  as_data_frame() %>% 
  column_to_rownames("gene_id") %>% 
  as.matrix() 
## Joining, by = "Sample"
## Joining, by = "Sample"
dds_gene <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = table_8M, 
                                   colData = metadata %>% filter(Respuesta == "NE" | Respuesta =="PE"), 
                                   design = ~Respuesta)
## converting counts to integer mode
## Warning in DESeqDataSet(se, design = design, ignoreRank): some variables in
## design formula are characters, converting to factors
dds_gene <- DESeq(dds_gene, fitType = "parametric", sfType = "poscount")
## estimating size factors
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
## -- replacing outliers and refitting for 21148 genes
## -- DESeq argument 'minReplicatesForReplace' = 7 
## -- original counts are preserved in counts(dds)
## estimating dispersions
## fitting model and testing
NE_vs_PE <- results(dds_gene, contrast = c("Respuesta","NE","PE"))

NE_vs_PE <- NE_vs_PE %>% 
  as_tibble(rownames = "ensembl_gene_id") %>%
    rename(fdr = padj) %>% 
  mutate(bonferroni = p.adjust(pvalue, method = "bonferroni")) %>% 
  mutate(homl = p.adjust(pvalue, method = "holm")) %>% 
  mutate(BY = p.adjust(pvalue, method = "BY")) %>% 
  filter(grepl("ENS",ensembl_gene_id)) %>% 
  mutate(ensembl_gene_id = str_replace(ensembl_gene_id,"\\.\\d+","")) %>% 
  inner_join(ttg)
## Joining, by = "ensembl_gene_id"
NE_vs_PE %>% 
  mutate(sig = ifelse(fdr < 0.001,"Significative","No-Significative")) %>%
  mutate(label = ifelse(sig == "Significative",external_gene_name,NA)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x= log2FoldChange, y = -log10(fdr), color = sig, size = sqrt(baseMean), label = label)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_text_repel(size = 1.5)+
  scale_color_d3() +
  theme_light() + labs(title = "NE vs PE")
## Warning: Removed 10361 rows containing missing values (geom_point).
## Warning: Removed 46815 rows containing missing values (geom_text_repel).
## Warning: ggrepel: 89 unlabeled data points (too many overlaps). Consider
## increasing max.overlaps

NE_vs_PE_enr <- NE_vs_PE %>% 
  filter(fdr < 0.001) %>% inner_join(ttg) %>% 
  dplyr::select(entrezgene_id) %>% distinct() %>% drop_na() %>%  pull(entrezgene_id)
## Joining, by = c("ensembl_gene_id", "external_gene_name", "description",
## "entrezgene_id")
NE_vs_PE_enr_go <- enrichGO(gene =NE_vs_PE_enr,
                                   OrgDb         = org.Hs.eg.db,
                                    ont           = "ALL",
                                    pAdjustMethod = "BH",
                                    pvalueCutoff  = 0.01,
                                    qvalueCutoff  = 0.05,
                                    readable      = TRUE)

if ((NE_vs_PE_enr_go %>% as.data.frame() %>% nrow()) > 0  )
{
  barplot(NE_vs_PE_enr_go, showCategory = 20)
} else{
  print("No enriched GO")
}
